article.headline: Arkansas St. 71, Tenn.-Martin 69
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Adrian Banks' last-second jumper gave Arkansas State a 71-69 win over Tennessee-Martin on Thursday. Banks contributed 22 points for the Indians (2-4), who led 38-35 at the half. Lester Hudson led Tennessee-Martin (3-4) with 28 points -- including six 3-pointers -- and 11 rebounds. The Skyhawks had just four assists in the game, along with 15 turnovers. Arkansas State led 63-56 with 6:10 remaining, but the Skyhawks slowly chipped away at the lead. Hudson made a 3-pointer and a layup on back-to-back possessions to narrow the lead to 67-66 with 1:56 left in the game. Ifeayni Koggu made a layup to put the Indians up 69-66, but Marquis Weddle nailed a 3-pointer to tie the game with 1:25 left. Banks' jumper with the time running out gave the Indians the win. Yima Chia-Kur added 11 points for the Indians, while Shawn Morgan had 12 points and 11 rebounds.
